<subSubSection id="C31C6500193CFFFB6A8BA74A7356F87D" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B193CFFFB6A8BA74A71E5F8D3" blockId="28.[189,457,1837,1863]" box="[189,457,1837,1863]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading id="D0F181E7193CFFFB6A8BA74A71E5F8D3" bold="true" box="[189,457,1837,1863]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA99193CFFFB6A8BA74A71E5F8D3" bold="true" box="[189,457,1837,1863]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B193CFFFB6A8BA7397356F87D" blockId="28.[189,1399,1886,2025]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
In addition to the characters in the key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D08193CFFFB68AAA7397460F8EC" authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[668,1100,1886,1912]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albolobata" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA99193CFFFB68AAA7397460F8EC" box="[668,1100,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) albolobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157E2193CFFFB6E60A739749EF8EC" box="[1110,1202,1886,1912]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D08193CFFFB6B2EA7E2719DF80A" authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[280,433,1924,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="licina" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA99193CFFFB6B2EA7E2719DF80A" box="[280,433,1924,1951]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. (A.) licina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157E2193CFFFB6B8DA7E37234F80A" box="[443,536,1924,1950]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having the ventral lobe of both gonostyli narrower, apicodorsal part of the right superior lobe shorter and by having the ventral part of the left superior lobe with more prominent anterior, medial and posterior lobes (
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E193CFFFB68DAA7A8731DF87D" box="[748,817,1999,2025]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[189,232,1927,1953]" captionTargetBox="[195,1394,992,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[189,1399,982,1897]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 7. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) albolobata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ. A. Posterior part of sternum IV, ventral view. B. Left surstylus, lateral view. C. Left superior lobe, lateral view. D. Genitalia, right side, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830553/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
<potCollectionCode id="59526885193CFFFB6907A7A87341F87D" box="[817,877,1999,2025]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">B–D</potCollectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C6500193DFFFA6A8BA16E7321FEE1" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B193DFFFA6A8BA16E7168FEB7" blockId="29.[189,324,265,291]" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<heading id="D0F181E7193DFFFA6A8BA16E7168FEB7" bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA99193DFFFA6A8BA16E7168FEB7" bold="true" box="[189,324,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B193DFFFA6A8BA15F7321FEE1" blockId="29.[189,1398,312,373]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D08193DFFFA689FA15F7304FEC6" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[681,808,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albolobata">
<emphasis id="B972EA99193DFFFA689FA15F7304FEC6" box="[681,808,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">albolobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘white-lobed’, referring to the white subtriangular lobe posteriorly on male sternum 
<potCollectionCode id="59526885193DFFFA68DCA13C7325FEE1" box="[746,777,347,373]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">IV</potCollectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
